  "text": "Archived microscope slides from 6-to 8-week-old female Syrian hamsters (HsdHan:AURA; Harlan Laboratories, Indianapolis, Indiana), from previously published studies, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] In the archived Nipah virus microscope slides, 5 hamsters were inoculated with NiV-M; 3 of these hamsters were euthanized at 2 dpi (case Nos. 1M-3M), and 2 hamsters (case Nos. 4M, 5M) were euthanized at 4 dpi. Eight hamsters were inoculated with NiV-B; 4 hamsters each were euthanized at 2 dpi (case Nos. 6B-9B) and 4 dpi (case Nos. 10B-13B). Examined tissues included the lung, nasal cavity (transverse or mid-sagittal sections through the skull), and brain. All tissues were analyzed for the presence of lesions and scored in a nonmasked manner by 2 pathologists (L.B., D.P.S.). Any discrepancies in scoring values were discussed and a final score was mutually agreed on by the pathologists. Lesion severity was scored as follows: 0 ¼ the lesion was absent, 1 ¼ up to 25% of the described tissue or cell type was affected, 2 ¼ up to 50% of the described tissue or cell type was affected, 3 ¼ up to 75% of the described tissue or cell type was affected, and 4 ¼ 75% to 100% of the described tissue or cell type was affected.",
